snippet.textDisplay:
Let me start by saying this ... I love Sam and Colby. I only found them last year but since then I have been following everything that they do and I have watched every single video they have posted and other video's that they have been in. I am a huge fan and I love their content and their story on how they got to where they are now. I am proud of them.


Now... I get Sam and Colby's side. I bet it is extremely frustrating for them to fly someone out to a destination and it seems like he is making fun of the situation and not really paying attention ... but then I also see it from everyone else's side and Jake really does make a point, if you want to make good ghost content you need to stay there and get actual answers. It's cool that they have gotten some things on tape and some voice recordings in the past, but what made Ghost Adventures successful and TAPS and all that, is actually staying there and gathering as much evidence as they can.


If doesn't feel like the same content anymore. They use to be skeptical and now they believe in it and that's cool and all but they need to provide better content then just running away from it. I feel bad for Corey because he is never going to get his closure and if he really wants it then I would suggest going to professionals. As for Sam and Colby, if they are too scared to make this type of content then maybe it's time to re brand themselves again, sadly. Maybe they should go back to exploring but find places that won't get them in trouble.


I know that they are moving to Hawaii and hopefully that gives them a fresh start and fresh ideas. More personal videos instead of series. More prank wars etc. I love these guys so much and it hurts to see that the comment section is full of negative feedback but it's for sure feedback that needs to be heard. We are the views, and sadly, this is not the content we want unless it gets better.


Sam and Colby, if you see this, I love you, keep your chins up and thank you for keeping us entertained.
